<p id=3D"mntl-sc-block_14-0" class=3D"comp mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html=
"> Hopefully, by now, you're interested in working in grams and wondering w=
here to buy a kitchen scale. My favorite and most used kitchen item is the =
Escali Primo Digital Kitchen Scale. This scale is easily found online or in=
 major department stores, comes in many colors, and is relatively inexpensi=
ve. Once you have a digital scale, getting started should be a breeze. If t=
he recipe you want to bake already provides weight measurements, you're on =
your way! However for most recipes that are not written in grams, you'll ne=
ed to first find a notepad or write directly on the recipe to convert the v=
olume measurement into grams or <a href=3D"https://www.allrecipes.com/artic=
le/cup-to-gram-conversions/" data-component=3D"link" data-source=3D"inlineL=
ink" data-type=3D"internalLink" data-ordinal=3D"1">ounces</a>. Refer to the=
 chart of basic conversions below to accomplish this step. Once you've conv=
erted your recipes and start using a scale, enjoy baking with ease and accu=
racy =E2=80=94 you will never go back to old fashioned cups and teaspoons a=
gain.
</p>
